full of treasure,

02:31.483 --> 02:35.119
like a solid gold bar of silver
or Picasso's TV.

02:35.154 --> 02:36.621
Oh, no, no, no.

02:36.655 --> 02:39.324
It is I who will be watching
Picasso's TV tonight!

02:41.393 --> 02:42.727
Looks like
you're not the only

02:42.761 --> 02:44.629
predatory opportunist
in town.

02:45.664 --> 02:47.065
There's other P.O.'s?!

02:47.099 --> 02:49.667
Uh-oh, better put on
my game shades.

02:56.775 --> 02:58.476
Do I hear $50? Let me get $50.

02:58.510 --> 02:59.444
Oh, yeah!

02:59.478 --> 03:00.745
$100. Is there $100 out there?

03:00.779 --> 03:02.246
Looking for $100.
Thank you!

03:02.281 --> 03:03.915
$150, $150.

03:03.949 --> 03:05.116
Do I have $200?

03:05.150 --> 03:06.985
$250. Do I hear...

03:07.019 --> 03:08.086
$350.
Yarr!

03:08.120 --> 03:09.821
Four. Do I hear $400?

03:09.855 --> 03:11.089
$450.
Bidding!

03:11.123 --> 03:12.256
$500.

03:12.291 --> 03:13.725
$550.
Skinner!

03:13.759 --> 03:15.493
$600.

03:15.527 --> 03:16.728
$650.

03:16.762 --> 03:18.630
$650 going once,
$650 going twice...

03:21.300 --> 03:24.068
$1,000.

03:24.103 --> 03:25.403
$1,000 going once, going twice.

03:25.437 --> 03:27.505
Sold to the man who didn't
wait for the bidding

03:27.539 --> 03:29.107
to get anywhere near $1,000!

03:29.141 --> 03:32.210
In the money game,
cash is king.

03:38.651 --> 03:41.753
We spent $1,000 on a
bunch of old boxes?

03:41.787 --> 03:43.688
You won't be laughing
when these boxes

03:43.722 --> 03:45.456
are full of
priceless treasures.

03:45.491 --> 03:48.059
I wasn't laughing,
I was being worried.

03:51.063 --> 03:52.363
Feather boas?

03:52.398 --> 03:54.332
Mine's full of
hand mirrors.

03:54.366 --> 03:56.501
I've got perfume spritzers.

03:56.535 --> 03:58.469
Makeup and baby oil.

03:58.504 --> 04:00.171
Tights? Robes?

04:00.205 --> 04:03.324
Oh, this stupid locker must have
belonged to some old lady.

04:03.359 --> 04:06.260
"Property of
Abraham J. Simpson"?

04:06.295 --> 04:08.162
This is Grampa's stuff.

04:08.197 --> 04:10.998
Why would my man-dad
have lady stuff?

04:11.033 --> 04:12.900
It's not all lady stuff.

04:12.935 --> 04:17.572
Look at all these
fitness publications.

04:18.574 --> 04:20.141
Beefcake mags?

04:21.810 --> 04:25.046
I think your dad might be gay.

04:25.080 --> 04:27.014
Oh, that's insane.

04:27.049 --> 04:29.167
My dad was
married to a woman

04:29.201 --> 04:32.620
who left him because he ignored
her needs for decades.

04:32.654 --> 04:36.991
Ah, my gay dad
is gay for gays.

04:43.365 --> 04:45.800
I think this is great.

04:45.834 --> 04:47.902
Old gay men
are adorable.

04:47.936 --> 04:51.038
Like wrinkle dogs in a
wrinkle dog calendar.

04:51.073 --> 04:53.040
Those are pretty cute.

04:53.075 --> 04:55.810
Your dad's been in the
closet for so long,

04:55.844 --> 04:59.197
he probably doesn't know how
tolerant society's become.

04:59.231 --> 05:03.701
They even had a gay float
in the Pride Parade last year.

05:03.736 --> 05:06.571
My dad has
always been so angry.

05:06.605 --> 05:08.873
Maybe if we help him
be who he is,

05:08.907 --> 05:10.608
he'll finally be happy.

05:10.642 --> 05:12.110
Oh, Homie,

05:12.144 --> 05:15.079
you're so enlightened.

05:18.317 --> 05:21.586
Yeah, gay rights
are human rights, baby.

05:25.124 --> 05:26.908
Are you sure you're not
just doing all this

05:26.942 --> 05:28.676
because it's cool
to be accepting

05:28.710 --> 05:30.077
of a gay family member?

05:30.112 --> 05:32.513
Oh, honey, that's
just silly.

05:32.548 --> 05:34.298
This'll show
Helen Lovejoy.

05:34.333 --> 05:37.435
Always bragging about
her he-she cousin.

05:37.469 --> 05:41.606
Abe, we found
your storage locker.

05:41.640 --> 05:42.940
It's okay, Dad.

05:42.975 --> 05:45.443
We know the truth,
and we love you.

05:45.477 --> 05:46.778
What?!

05:46.812 --> 05:49.430
The contents of that locker
are my private business!

05:49.465 --> 05:50.598
Get out!

05:50.632 --> 05:51.966
Just admit who you are,

05:52.000 --> 05:54.101
and you can find new love.

05:54.136 --> 05:56.037
If you don't
want to die alone,

05:56.071 --> 05:58.239
come out of your room.

05:58.273 --> 06:01.709
Love... love...

06:01.760 --> 06:03.344
love... love...

06:06.265 --> 06:07.715
Hi, Marge.

06:07.749 --> 06:10.785
I was just taking Stanlerina
to get her hormone shots.

06:10.819 --> 06:11.986
Oh.

06:12.020 --> 06:14.388
Your father wasted
his whole life being married

06:14.423 --> 06:16.157
to your mother
and having you.

06:16.191 --> 06:19.260
We've got to find him a
boyfriend before it's too late.

06:19.294 --> 06:21.596
Why don't you put a
personal ad on the Internet?

06:21.630 --> 06:23.664
That's how young people
date these days.

06:23.699 --> 06:24.832
It's weird that you don't

06:24.867 --> 06:26.567
consider yourself
a young person.

06:26.602 --> 06:27.401
I know.

06:27.436 --> 06:28.603
It's weird to me, too.

06:28.637 --> 06:30.671
"Help me out of the closet.

06:30.706 --> 06:33.274
"Wonderful older man
seeks life partner

06:33.308 --> 06:35.810
before rapidly-encroaching
death."

06:35.844 --> 06:36.911
No fatties.

06:36.945 --> 06:38.613
How about <i>some</i> fatties?

06:38.647 --> 06:39.614
Fine.

06:39.648 --> 06:41.015
Okay, post this under

06:41.049 --> 06:42.817
"Men Seeking Men."

06:42.851 --> 06:44.285
But what subheading?

06:44.319 --> 06:45.920
Hmm, nothing too serious.

06:45.954 --> 06:48.923
Here we go, "Casual Encounters."

06:48.957 --> 06:51.959
Perfect! No pressure.

06:53.228 --> 06:54.929
I hope someone
saw our ad.

06:54.963 --> 06:57.698
If I can't find my father a man
to kiss and cuddle,

06:57.733 --> 06:59.333
then I've failed as a son.

07:00.569 --> 07:01.569
Someone's coming.

07:02.871 --> 07:05.373
Are you
"Wrinkled and Romantic"?

07:05.407 --> 07:08.009
Huh? What the heck are you
talking about, Spectacles?

07:08.043 --> 07:10.211
Oh, I've been hung up
on someone for years,

07:10.245 --> 07:12.346
but I'm trapped
in the friend zone.

07:12.381 --> 07:14.448
It's time for me to move on.

07:14.483 --> 07:15.516
So move on.

07:15.551 --> 07:16.717
You're blocking the ducks.

07:16.752 --> 07:18.920
Don't you want
to be happy, Abe?

07:18.954 --> 07:22.690
Admit who you are,
a wonderful gay man.

07:24.343 --> 07:25.443
What?!

07:25.477 --> 07:27.144
I don't ride sidesaddle!

07:27.179 --> 07:29.013
I'm straight as a submarine!

07:29.047 --> 07:31.482
Then how do you
explain this?

07:31.516 --> 07:33.117
Oh, hello, Smithers.

07:33.151 --> 07:36.053
Fancy seeing you
in Casual Encounter Park.

07:38.257 --> 07:40.274
You're Glamorous Godfrey!

07:40.309 --> 07:41.976
Who?

07:42.010 --> 07:44.612
Glamorous Godfrey was the most
famous wrestler in the world.

07:44.646 --> 07:45.880
And you are he!

07:45.914 --> 07:47.715
Is this true?

07:47.749 --> 07:49.617
Behold.

07:49.651 --> 07:51.085
Look at
all this wrestling crap.

07:51.119 --> 07:52.236
Ah.
<i>Ay, caramba!</i>

07:52.271 --> 07:54.972
Fine, I was Glamorous Godfrey.

07:57.175 --> 07:58.209
What's wrong?

07:58.243 --> 08:01.045
I so wanted
him to be gay.

08:01.079 --> 08:04.081
Well, on V.E. Day, I
kissed a man by mistake.

08:04.116 --> 08:05.449
Thank you.

08:07.612 --> 08:09.647
You were
a world-famous wrestler?

08:09.681 --> 08:11.482
Spill the beans, old man.

08:11.516 --> 08:12.650
Word beans!

08:12.684 --> 08:14.885
Oh, all right, I'll tell you.

08:14.920 --> 08:17.021
It was the 1950s.

08:17.055 --> 08:19.056
Oh, those things?

08:19.091 --> 08:21.492
It <i>was the heyday</i>
<i>of pro wrestling.</i>

08:21.526 --> 08:24.261
<i>You could make good money</i>
<i>if you were the manly mixture</i>

08:24.296 --> 08:26.731
<i>of strong and fat</i>
<i>we called beefy.</i>

08:26.765 --> 08:30.534
<i>Good guys were called</i>
<i>"baby faces."</i>

08:30.569 --> 08:33.320
<i>And bad guys</i>
<i>were called "heels."</i>

08:33.355 --> 08:37.224
<i>I was the king of the heels,</i>
<i>Glamorous Godfrey.</i>

08:37.259 --> 08:38.509
How dare he!

08:38.543 --> 08:40.410
That was drinking milk!

08:40.445 --> 08:42.897
<i>My motto was "Always cheat."</i>

08:48.136 --> 08:52.957
<i>But the thing that really drove</i>
<i>them crazy was my vanity.</i>

08:52.991 --> 08:55.893
You are the luckiest people
in the world.

08:55.927 --> 08:58.062
You get to look at me.

09:02.501 --> 09:05.736
Grampa, you were
the original bad boy.

09:05.771 --> 09:09.540
Yeah, I was boastful before
all your football showboaters,

09:09.574 --> 09:12.359
rap music-ers and
TV beach Italians.

09:12.394 --> 09:15.262
