Why do you think
bad guys are so cool?

14:28.111 --> 14:30.279
Why do you still have
a thing for Nelson?

14:30.313 --> 14:32.114
I'm not!
That's ridiculous!

14:32.149 --> 14:34.433
I just...
it's that... he, uh...

14:34.468 --> 14:37.119
He's a rebel,
and only I can change him!

14:57.707 --> 14:59.808
It's so sad that
Grampa has to cheat

14:59.843 --> 15:02.878
instead of relying on his
God-given wrestling skills.

15:02.913 --> 15:05.948
What kind of person
revels in disapproval?

15:05.982 --> 15:09.785
What kind of
person, indeed.

15:13.990 --> 15:17.960
It's the prettiest boy
in Springfield, Bart Simpson!

15:17.994 --> 15:19.695
What's going on?

15:23.567 --> 15:26.135
You are the luckiest people
in the world!

15:26.169 --> 15:27.570
You get to look at me!

15:31.758 --> 15:33.058
Hey!

15:37.531 --> 15:39.932
Hey, Simpson, tell your
kid to quit showboating.

15:39.966 --> 15:43.469
I've never seen anyone
so full of self-regard!

15:43.503 --> 15:46.639
And I've worked
with Bob Balaban!

15:52.829 --> 15:55.764
Your behavior at that
game was unacceptable!

15:55.799 --> 15:58.817
You're lucky they gave you
your participant trophy!

15:58.852 --> 16:01.186
I got one
just for watching the game.

16:03.189 --> 16:05.991
Listen, getting people riled up
is what heels do.

16:06.026 --> 16:07.626
Heel? Oh, no.

16:07.661 --> 16:09.662
Tell me you're not
trying to be like Grampa!

16:09.696 --> 16:11.096
Well, sure I am.

16:11.131 --> 16:12.698
I always thought
Grampa was lame,

16:12.732 --> 16:14.433
but he's
really awesome!

16:14.467 --> 16:16.569
Your grandfather
is super lame!

16:16.603 --> 16:19.371
I mean, if he wasn't
a terrible father,

16:19.406 --> 16:21.507
what's my excuse for this?

16:24.878 --> 16:27.413
I know your grandpa
seems exciting now,

16:27.447 --> 16:29.915
but all that preening
and cheating--

16:29.950 --> 16:33.786
those turnbuckle antics are
not gonna make him happy.

16:36.306 --> 16:38.240
Burnsy, I can't
remember the last time

16:38.275 --> 16:40.259
I was so happy!

16:41.394 --> 16:43.362
You grandson-
ruining fiend!

16:43.396 --> 16:45.414
Look what your
number one fan

16:45.448 --> 16:47.049
did at show-and-tell!

16:48.118 --> 16:49.785
Wait. Ow.

16:49.819 --> 16:51.854
Ah. Wait.

16:51.888 --> 16:53.856
Who would film
such a thing?

16:53.890 --> 16:55.374
It's found footage!

16:55.408 --> 16:58.143
So what? We could use
another winner in this family!

16:58.178 --> 16:59.595
How are you
a winner?

16:59.629 --> 17:01.597
You're cheating
in a fake sport.

17:01.631 --> 17:02.931
Fake? Ridiculous.

17:02.966 --> 17:04.583
If professional wrestling
were fake,

17:04.617 --> 17:07.486
that would make every fan
in the history of the sport

17:07.520 --> 17:09.954
a complete and utter moron.

17:11.590 --> 17:12.958
Mercy.

17:12.992 --> 17:16.028
You know, I've always had
a keen eye for tiny talent.

17:16.061 --> 17:18.464
Perhaps you and the lad
could tag-team up.

17:18.498 --> 17:19.798
Wrestle with Bart?

17:19.833 --> 17:22.800
Well, he ain't beefy,
but he is infuriating,

17:22.836 --> 17:24.703
and you can't
teach infuriating.

17:24.738 --> 17:26.805
Monty, you're
a genius!

17:26.839 --> 17:29.308
Bart cannot be an
old-time wrestler!

17:29.342 --> 17:33.362
As your inattentive son, and
your incompetent employee,

17:33.396 --> 17:34.913
I forbid it!

17:34.948 --> 17:39.084
Oh, why does everything
I forbid always happen?

17:44.599 --> 17:47.267
So, Beautiful,
you got your moves memorized?

17:47.301 --> 17:48.935
You know it,
Glamorous!

17:48.970 --> 17:50.704
Eye gouge! Ear bite!
Folding chair!

17:50.738 --> 17:52.839
Hair pull! Face-fart!
Flying face-fart!

17:52.874 --> 17:54.858
And then I start
fighting dirty.

17:56.043 --> 17:57.778
They're gonna
hate you so much.

17:59.197 --> 18:00.764
Oh, I get it.

18:00.798 --> 18:04.401
You're here to tell the kid he
can't wrestle with his grandpa.

18:06.554 --> 18:08.872
I don't care if Bart
is a wrestler,

18:08.906 --> 18:13.210
a busboy, or even
a stoplight squeegee man,

18:13.244 --> 18:16.046
as long as
he's a nice person.

18:16.080 --> 18:18.949
But if he gets too much
attention for acting bad,

18:18.983 --> 18:21.735
he might turn bad
on the inside.

18:21.769 --> 18:23.653
Eh, that's women-talk.

18:23.688 --> 18:27.557
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I have to comb out my curls!

18:27.592 --> 18:30.961
One... two... three...

18:33.865 --> 18:37.067
Beautiful Bart,
can I have your autograph?

18:37.101 --> 18:38.902
Sure. Here you go.

18:42.573 --> 18:44.107
Eh, hey, Bart,

18:44.142 --> 18:46.543
leave some of that bad
attitude for the ring.

18:46.577 --> 18:48.945
The world is my ring now.

18:54.218 --> 18:56.853
In this corner,
for truth and justice,

18:56.888 --> 18:58.688
Captain Flag and Half-Mast.

19:00.725 --> 19:04.094
Now entering the ring,
the first family of foul play,

19:04.128 --> 19:06.396
Glamorous Godfrey
and Beautiful Bart!

19:09.717 --> 19:11.384
You all stink!

19:17.508 --> 19:20.527
Glamorous Godfrey is dead!

19:24.148 --> 19:26.783
I am Honest Abe!

19:30.488 --> 19:33.623
And this is Laddie Liberty!

19:33.658 --> 19:35.192
What are you doing?

19:35.226 --> 19:37.510
I ain't a heel no more,
I'm a good guy.

19:37.545 --> 19:38.945
And you're a baby-face.

19:38.980 --> 19:40.480
But-but what about
the cheating?

19:40.514 --> 19:41.548
No more cheating.

19:41.582 --> 19:42.649
And the preening?

19:42.683 --> 19:43.817
No more preening.

19:43.851 --> 19:45.051
But I'm so pretty.

19:45.086 --> 19:47.287
That's for others to say now.

19:47.321 --> 19:49.022
What are you doing,
Godfrey?

19:49.056 --> 19:52.292
You're a villain, not some
bullet-brained rail-splitter.

19:52.326 --> 19:55.312
Without someone to hate, there's
no excitement, no thrill.

19:55.346 --> 19:57.981
I don't care.
My grandson's soul is at stake.

19:58.015 --> 20:00.317
How dare you.
I wrote a song for you.

20:00.351 --> 20:02.636
When am I ever
going to use that again?

20:02.670 --> 20:05.972
Curse you, and this
morbidly obese little half-wit.

20:07.174 --> 20:10.360
So, they only want
to see a good guy

20:10.394 --> 20:12.195
fight a bad guy, eh?

20:13.848 --> 20:16.066
Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa...

20:17.752 --> 20:19.703
He's taking on Mean Man Monty!

20:19.737 --> 20:21.538
Go get him, Honest Abe!

20:21.572 --> 20:23.840
This is why we go to
everything in this town--

20:23.874 --> 20:25.225
it always pays off.

20:28.195 --> 20:29.813
Honest Abe,
can I pin him?

20:29.847 --> 20:32.749
Ha-ha! You know it,
Laddie Liberty!

20:40.558 --> 20:43.226
Damndest boos
I ever heard.

20:43.261 --> 20:45.095
They're cheering, Grampa.

20:45.129 --> 20:48.265
This is what I've been
missing my whole life.

20:50.301 --> 20:52.769
Oh, that was so sweet.

20:53.871 --> 20:56.439
I wish Grampa was <i>my</i> dad.

